---
import Chapter from '../../layouts/Chapter.astro';
const lds = [{"@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "BreadcrumbList", "itemListElement": [{"@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://patrick.realestate/"}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Neighborhoods", "item": "https://patrick.realestate/neighborhoods"}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Glencoe", "item": "https://patrick.realestate/neighborhoods/glencoe"}]}, {"@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Place", "name": "Glencoe, Illinois", "url": "https://patrick.realestate/neighborhoods/glencoe", "containedInPlace": {"@type": "Place", "name": "North Shore, Chicago, IL"}}];
---
<Chapter
  title="Glencoe — Patrick Milhaupt · North Shore"
  description="Glencoe village brief — lakefront ravines, classic Glencoe brick, the Chicago Botanic Garden anchor, and the corridor's most consistently appreciating sub-market."
  path="/neighborhoods/glencoe" current="/neighborhoods" palette="0.15"
  jsonLd={lds.length>=1 ? lds[0] : null}
  rail={[{"id": "ch-00", "num": "00", "label": "Opening"}, {"id": "ch-01", "num": "01", "label": "Snapshot"}, {"id": "ch-02", "num": "02", "label": "Architecture"}, {"id": "ch-03", "num": "03", "label": "Begin"}]}
>


  <section class="chapter" id="ch-00" data-chapter="0" data-palette="0.15">
    <div class="inner" style="text-align:center; align-items:center;">
      <div class="ch-head fade-up" style="justify-content:center;">
        <span class="hashmark"><i></i></span>
        <div class="meta" style="border:0; padding:0;">
          <span class="eyebrow">Glencoe &middot; North Shore</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h1 class="headline" data-headline="">
        Ravine houses and the <em>Botanic Garden</em>.
      </h1>
      <p class="body fade-up" style="margin: 0 auto; text-align:center;">
        Glencoe is the corridor's lakefront-ravine village &mdash; defined as much by its topography as by its architecture. The Chicago Botanic Garden anchors the northern edge, and the village has been among the steadiest-appreciating sub-markets on the North Shore across the past decade.
      </p>
      <div class="cta-row fade-up" style="justify-content:center;">
        <a class="btn" href="#ch-01">View the snapshot &darr;</a>
        <a class="btn btn-outline" href="/intelligence#ch-02">Open live dashboard</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="chapter" id="ch-01" data-chapter="1" data-palette="0.40">
    <div class="inner">
      <div class="ch-head fade-up">
        <span class="num">01</span>
        <div class="meta">
          <span class="eyebrow">Chapter One</span>
          <span class="sub">Glencoe Snapshot</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="headline" data-headline="">
        A village of <em>ravines</em>, brick, and consistency.
      </h2>
      <p class="body fade-up">
        Glencoe's median list price of $1.95M sits squarely between Winnetka's tightness and Lake Forest's range. Days-on-market average 28, sale-to-list ratios run a healthy 98.6%, and price-per-square-foot lands at $548. The defining village-level fact, however, is appreciation consistency &mdash; Glencoe has produced the steadiest year-over-year price growth on the corridor across the last decade, with shallower drawdowns and faster recoveries than its neighbors.
      </p>
      <div class="kpi-grid">
        <div class="kpi"><span class="l">Median Price</span><span class="v" style="font-size:22px;">$1.95M</span><span class="d">Village-wide list median</span></div>
        <div class="kpi"><span class="l">Days on Market</span><span class="v" style="font-size:22px;">28 days</span><span class="d">Healthy pace, well-priced inventory</span></div>
        <div class="kpi pop"><span class="l">SP/OLP</span><span class="v" style="font-size:22px;">98.6%</span><span class="d up">Sale-to-list ratio</span></div>
        <div class="kpi"><span class="l">$/SqFt</span><span class="v" style="font-size:22px;">$548</span><span class="d up">Premium for ravine &amp; lake parcels</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="market-blend" style="padding:16px 24px 56px;">
  <div style="max-width:1120px;margin:0 auto;background:#0A1838;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.08);border-radius:16px;padding:22px 22px 12px;box-shadow:0 24px 70px rgba(0,0,0,.35);">
    <div id="blendedMarket"></div>
  </div>
</section>

  <section class="chapter" id="ch-02" data-chapter="2" data-palette="0.65">
    <div class="inner">
      <div class="ch-head fade-up">
        <span class="num">02</span>
        <div class="meta">
          <span class="eyebrow">Chapter Two</span>
          <span class="sub">Architecture &amp; Schools</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="headline" data-headline="">
        Brick <em>vocabulary</em>, anchor schools.
      </h2>
      <p class="body fade-up">
        Glencoe's architectural character is shaped by its topography &mdash; the <strong>ravines that bisect the village from the lake inland</strong> have produced a distinct sub-genre of "ravine house," sited on bridged or cantilevered lots above wooded gorges. The dominant building material is the warm brick that gives the village its visual signature, with significant inventory of Tudor revival, mid-century moderns sited into the ravines, and a smaller cohort of contemporary lakefront commissions. The Chicago Botanic Garden on the northern edge is a defining civic asset.
      </p>
      <p class="body fade-up">
        Glencoe's K&ndash;8 students attend <strong>Glencoe District 35</strong> &mdash; a small, well-resourced district that feeds into <strong>New Trier Township High School (District 203)</strong>. The pairing of an intimate K&ndash;8 experience with the New Trier anchor is one of the most-cited reasons families select Glencoe over its neighbors.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="chapter" id="ch-03" data-chapter="3" data-palette="1.00">
    <div class="inner" style="text-align:center; align-items:center;">
      <div class="ch-head fade-up" style="justify-content:center;">
        <span class="num">03</span>
        <div class="meta">
          <span class="eyebrow">Begin</span>
          <span class="sub">A 30-minute call</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="headline" data-headline="">
        Move in <em>Glencoe</em>.
      </h2>
      <p class="body fade-up" style="margin: 0 auto; text-align:center;">
        Thirty minutes. We'll walk through current inventory, the ravine-versus-non-ravine pricing differential, and an honest forward read on the next three to six months. No pitch.
      </p>
      <div class="begin-block fade-up">
        <div class="col"><div class="l">Direct</div><div class="v"><a href="tel:+18478499828" style="color:inherit;text-decoration:none;">(847) 849-9828</a></div></div>
        <div class="col"><div class="l">Email</div><div class="v"><a href="mailto:pmilhaupt@jamesonsir.com">pmilhaupt@jamesonsir.com</a></div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="cta-row fade-up" style="justify-content:center; margin-top: 32px;">
        <a class="btn" href="mailto:pmilhaupt@jamesonsir.com">Schedule the Call &rarr;</a>
        <a class="btn btn-outline" href="/neighborhoods">Back to neighborhoods</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <script slot="head" type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(lds[1])} />
  <script slot="scripts" src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/d3/7.9.0/d3.min.js" is:inline></script>
  <script slot="scripts" src="/brand/charts/d3-brand.js" is:inline></script>
</Chapter>
